## Exercise 3.3: An Intro to JavaScript / jQuery
* Styling is great, but has its limits. Enter JavaScript, the primary language used to manipulate DOM elements.


For this assignment, let's connect JS to the HTML and explore one of the most common "events", the "click event".
1. Set up a basic HTML document using the basic template we have used on previous exercises
2. Add two main elements to the page. A button that will be clicked and another square that will start one color and change when the other button is clicked.
3. Add the jQuery code to your document in a `<script>` tag using the jQuery CDN
4. Use jQuery selectors and the jQuery click event to change the button color


